args: ...Ma'am? Is this visitor here\nto see you, too?
That's rightâ€”and he's got great news!
This man wants to become our patron!
Absolutely! I first had the honor to witness\none of your shows the other day,\nand what a spectacle it was!
My pulse was pounding from beginning\nto end! Oh my, yes.
So deeply moved was I by what I saw,\nI decided I simply MUST do something\nto support your continued efforts.
In particular, I was astounded by your\ndagger-throwing skills, young man.\nThey are simply incredible!
I can certainly see why you have the\nbacking of an Alberian prince.
Knowing that, I couldn't help\nbut have an idea...
Would it not be an incredible sight for\nyour royal backer to ascend the stage\nbeside you?
Indeed! I would love to see an act starring\nyourself and this dagger-thrower!
If you can see this done, I will spare no\ncoin or effort in your support! Huzzah!\nHuzzah, I say!
You two would be performing,\nso it's really up to you.
I'm happy to do anything that helps\nyour troupe.
And I'm just a performer, so I'll abide\nby the wishes of our ringmaster and \nnew benefactor.
Then here is an advance payment.\nAs for the details of the performance...
Not too late to call this off if you're\nnervous, {player_name}.
I seriously have no idea what that noble\nwas thinking when he proposed this.
No, I'm fine. I believe in your skills.
Yeah, I don't think I'm going to miss, but...\nOh, we're up. Let's do this.
Thank you all for your patience!
It's time for the highlight of today's showâ€”\na performance starring myself and\nPrince {player_name}!
He has agreed to allow us to do the\nunthinkable! We will bind his limbs\nwith ropes to that target over there...
And then I will cut those ropes\nusing my daggers!
Should I miss by even a hair's width,\nthe prince's very life could be in peril!
I hope you all enjoy this nail-biting\nperformance!
(Oh, how I have waited for this chance!)
(My assassins are going to take his life\nby throwing daggers from the shadows,\nand that fool will take the blame!)
(Everyone will just think this was all a\ntragic accident! Aaaah ha ha ha!)
Did you see that, ladies and gentlemen?\nA dagger that is not my own flew onto\nthe stage from the darkness!
It seems simply binding the prince\nis not thrilling enough.
As such, I will sever the ropes that bind\nhim while repelling the daggers thrown\nfrom the shadows!
(That man was after the prince's life\nfrom the very start!)
(Well, he's about to learn what I can\nREALLY do.)
Behold your prince, unharmed and free!
Let's have a thunderous round of applause\nfor our brave volunteer!
Where did all those extra daggers\ncome from, Fritz?
Shh! Backstage, quickly!\nYou're too exposed here!
I can't believe he managed to repel\nALL of those daggers!
And here I thought you came to me\nBECAUSE of my skills.
Eeek! Wh-what are you doing here?!
So you wanted to kill the prince and\nmake me your patsy, did you?
I...I haven't the faintest idea\nwhat you are talking about, sir!
You're a real scumbag, you know that?\nIf you'd pulled that off, I would have\nregretted that show for the rest of my life.
How dare you refer to your patron thus?!
Oh, you can have your money backâ€”\nI won't take a single red cent from\na lump of human garbage like you!
I've had enough of your smart mouth.\nCome, my assassins! Cut this fool down!
Because we captured all of them.\nIt's time to answer for your crimes.
Were you asleep at the start of the show?\nï¼‚No matter the target or the situation,\nI never miss what I set my eyes on.ï¼‚
You can find your minions in the forest.\nI pinned 'em all to trees. Kept 'em alive,\ntooâ€”not that they deserved it.
You're not much of a tree decoration,\nbut it'll have to do.
I DO hope you aren't thinking\nyou'll get away with this!
I could say the same to you.
Not after you tried to use our circus\nfor a regicide.
Now, where should I target next?\nMaybe that big fat belly of yours?\nOr do I just go straight for the heart?
Eeeek! I'm sorry! I'm sorry!\nPlease don't kill me!
Never come near any of us ever again.\nIf you agree to that, we'll let you go.
Not many folks would show mercy to\na cat that tried to do 'em in.
I think he learned his lesson.
Besides, I didn't want you to have to\nuse your daggers to hurt people again.
I see. Well, we're done here,\nso let's get back to the castle.
